headline: Does Allstate’s Recent Outperformance Signal Room for Further Growth in 2025?
summary: If you’re sitting there staring at Allstate’s stock chart, wondering if now is the moment to buy, sell, or just hold tight, you’re in good company. Allstate has been quietly racking up some impressive gains over the years. Did you know the stock is up 154.5% over the last five years? Even just this year, it has delivered a 7.1% return, despite dipping a modest 1.5% over the past week. These moves suggest investors are reassessing both the risks and the long-term growth prospects of this...
